# Mushajjir ‚Äî CLI Agent Rules

## Project Overview
- Vue 3 + Vite + Pinia SPA
- Vue Flow canvas for node-based tree editing
- localStorage-based persistence (no backend)
- AI integration via OpenAI-compatible APIs (OpenRouter, DeepSeek, Grok)

## Conventions

### Code Style
- Use `eslint.config.js` (flat config) ‚Äî ESLint v10 no longer supports `.eslintrc.*`
- Run `npm run lint` before committing; 0 errors required
- Run `npm run format` (Prettier) before committing
- Semi: false, singleQuote: true, trailingComma: all, printWidth: 120
- Self-closing void elements (`<input/>`) are used consistently ‚Äî `vue/html-self-closing` is disabled
- Intentional `v-html` usage (markdown rendering) must be preceded by `<!-- eslint-disable-next-line vue/no-v-html -->`

### Git Workflow
- Local repo uses git worktrees ‚Äî check `git remote -v` and `git log --oneline -3` before assuming state
- Always `git fetch origin` first and check `git log --oneline origin/main..HEAD` for divergence
- If local is behind: `git stash` ‚Üí `git pull --rebase origin main` ‚Üí `git stash pop`
- Never use `git format-patch` + `git am` across diverged branches ‚Äî conflicts are guaranteed
- After merging/rebase, re-run `npm run lint -- --fix` and `npm run format`

### Editor Tooling
- The `editor` tool's `old_text ‚Üí new_text` replacement can corrupt indentation in `.vue` files
- Always run `npx prettier --write <file>` after using the editor tool on `.vue` files
- Prefer `run_commands` with `sed` or `cat` for precise line-level changes in complex files

### Dependencies
- Check versions before creating config files (e.g., ESLint v9+ uses flat config)
- Use `npm install --save-dev` for dev dependencies
- Semver ranges in package.json: use `^` for libraries, `latest` for apps (as is current convention)

### ESM Imports
- ALL local `.js` file imports MUST include the `.js` extension (Node.js ESM requirement)
- Example: `import { foo } from '../utils/treeUtils.js'` ‚Äî NOT `'../utils/treeUtils'`
- Vue component imports use `.vue` extension: `import Foo from './Foo.vue'`

### Config Constants
- Configuration data lives in `src/config/index.js`
- Current exports: `TASK_STATUSES`, `DEFAULT_TAGS`, `NODE_SIZE`, `MAX_CHILDREN`
- `src/utils/treeUtils.js` re-exports `TASK_STATUSES` and `DEFAULT_TAGS` for backward compatibility
- New config values should be added to `src/config/index.js`, not to utility files

### Architecture Docs
- Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) live in `doc/adr/`
- See `doc/architecture-reference.md` for component hierarchy and data flow
- See `doc/performance-budget.md` for performance targets

### Issues
- Close issues with `gh issue close <number>` after pushing
- Use `gh issue view <number>` to read issue details
